brewers, particularly in Western countries.</p><p> Investments have also been made in new technology to expedite the brewing process, including the utilization of &#39;BeerBots&#39; capable of accelerating the fermentation process.</p><p> According to Future Market Insights, the global beer market is <a href="https://www.futuremarketinsights.com/reports/beer-market">projected</a> to be valued at $690 billion in 2023, rising to $996 billion by 2033.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/which-countries-drink-the-most-beer-2/">Ranked: Which Countries Drink the Most Beer?</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com">Visual Capitalist</a> .</p> ; https://www.visualcapitalist.com/which-countries-drink-the-most-beer-2/feed/ 0 160478
